Activityc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Activity

An activity is something that occurs over a period of time and acts upon or with entities; it may include consuming, processing, transforming, modifying, relocating, using, or generating entities.

has sub-classes
Claim Evaluation Activityc, Selection Activityc, Verification Activityc
is in domain of
has next activityop, has previous activityop, has time intervalop, is activity of planop, qualified associationop, usedop, was associated withop
is in range of
has activityop, has next activityop, has previous activityop, was generated byop
is disjoint with
Agentc, Entityc

Agentc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Agent

An agent is something that bears some form of responsibility for an activity taking place, for the existence of an entity, or for another agent's activity.

has sub-classes
Evidence Sourcec, Organizationc, Personc, Personc, Software Agentc
is in domain of
affiliated toop
is in range of
affiliated toop, agentop, was associated withop, was attributed toop
has members

Associationc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Association

An activity association is an assignment of responsibility to an agent for an activity, indicating that the agent had a role in the activity. It further allows for a plan to be specified, which is the plan intended by the agent to achieve some goals in the context of this activity.

is in domain of
agentop, had roleop
is in range of
qualified associationop
